You will always be able to understand which competencies and which methods you have the opportunity to assess.

00:30.000 --> 00:36.000
I would like to draw your attention to the slide where, as an example, the competence of working with clients is given,

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
and the methods of assessment that the company has in stock are listed.

00:41.000 --> 00:45.000
This is from the filling of the assessment sheet by the 360-degree method,

00:45.000 --> 00:51.000
and as we can see that instead of the subordinate, the client is participating here, assessing the employee.

00:51.000 --> 00:55.000
This can be a written assessment of the knowledge of the assortment and the work technique,

00:55.000 --> 00:58.000
work with clients, that is, an assessment of knowledge.

00:58.000 --> 01:03.000
This is a business game that is developed based on the situation that took place.

01:03.000 --> 01:07.000
And also this is a case that is offered to the participants to decide.

01:07.000 --> 01:14.000
Again, someone else for this competence can offer some other methods.

01:14.000 --> 01:18.000
Maybe there will be only two of them, maybe three, and they will be completely different.

01:18.000 --> 01:22.000
In this case, we see a choice of a specific company.

01:22.000 --> 01:27.000
When the staff understands that in order to assess the competence of working with our employees,

01:27.000 --> 01:31.000
these methods are available.

01:31.000 --> 01:34.000
So, we have assessed our employees.

01:34.000 --> 01:44.000
We have laid out the requirements for the level of development or the profile of the position on our axes,

01:45.000 --> 01:50.000
and then applied the current level of competence development of our employees.

01:50.000 --> 01:56.000
We receive information for analysis, and we need to use this information.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
How can we use it?

01:58.000 --> 02:04.000
We can either make an individual plan and programs for each employee.

02:04.000 --> 02:11.000
We determine which employees we will represent in the personnel reserve.

02:11.000 --> 02:17.000
Speaking of the personnel reserve, it is important to understand that if we define a group for ourselves,

02:17.000 --> 02:21.000
the group can be very large, or the positions can be different.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
This does not mean that we have presented the whole group in the reserve for all positions.

02:25.000 --> 02:26.000
Absolutely not.

02:26.000 --> 02:31.000
We remember that in order to be listed in the personnel reserve and for subsequent development,

02:31.000 --> 02:37.000
it is necessary to assess, or assess again, or impose the assessment that we have made,

02:37.000 --> 02:43.000
but already to the level, to the profile of competence of the position under which we select the reserve.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
This does not mean that everything is again, everything is from the beginning.

02:47.000 --> 02:57.000
Because if we represent an employee in the reserve, in, say, a higher position,

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
then these are positions within the same group of positions.

03:00.000 --> 03:05.000
Therefore, there will be the same corporate competencies, the same professional competencies.

03:05.000 --> 03:09.000
The only thing that can be added is managerial competencies.

03:09.000 --> 03:14.000
If the employee did not engage in management activities in the previous position,

03:14.000 --> 03:21.000
so we can or plan to list those people whom we list in the personnel reserve.

03:21.000 --> 03:25.000
We suggest that they go through another exercise,

03:25.000 --> 03:31.000
within which we will observe the level of development of their management competencies for subsequent assessment.

03:32.000 --> 03:35.000
The next one is the planning of the employee's career.

03:35.000 --> 03:40.000
This is an opportunity that we have, and we can understand and give feedback to the employee

03:40.000 --> 03:43.000
so that he understands what he can expect while working in our company.

03:43.000 --> 03:46.000
This is the adjustment of compensation packages.

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
Here I also say, because the word adjustment is very soft,

03:50.000 --> 03:53.000
this is by no means a change in compensation packages.

03:53.000 --> 03:54.000
What does this mean?

03:54.000 --> 03:59.000
I do not recommend you to change the labor payment system,

03:59.000 --> 04:04.000
to increase the salary based on the results of the assessment of competencies.

04:04.000 --> 04:09.000
Because we pay for the result, and competencies are still behavior.

04:09.000 --> 04:15.000
We should not pay for the demonstrated behavior, no matter how it sounds.

04:15.000 --> 04:22.000
It is clear that if the assessment of competencies is accompanied by the assessment of activity,

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
then it can be the next step.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
In any case, be careful.

04:26.000 --> 04:32.000
Remember that only for the results of the assessment of the assessment center,

04:32.000 --> 04:35.000
compensation packages should not be changed easily.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
There should be some other reason for this.

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
Let's talk about the use of competencies in the development of personnel.

04:42.000 --> 04:46.000
We have done a lot of work, we have evaluated,

04:46.000 --> 04:50.000
and we understand that there is a group of employees with a number of competencies,

04:50.000 --> 04:53.000
which we need to improve.

04:53.000 --> 04:54.000
We all together.

04:54.000 --> 04:55.000
It is clear that they need to be improved.

04:55.000 --> 04:58.000
But we, if we are a personnel service,

04:58.000 --> 05:05.000
need to create an environment and provide the tools that will help employees do this.

05:05.000 --> 05:10.000
First of all, we develop special training programs,

05:10.000 --> 05:14.000
whether individual or group, for the development of competencies.

05:14.000 --> 05:19.000
We can do this within our training centers or within the company,

05:19.000 --> 05:24.000
or we can attract external partners to achieve these goals.

05:24.000 --> 05:28.000
There are many methods of training, they are different.

05:28.000 --> 05:33.000
They are different in quality, they are different in duration, they are different in cost.

05:33.000 --> 05:40.000
Again, from these methods, we choose those that are acceptable for the development of specific competencies,

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
specific employees in our companies.

05:43.000 --> 05:47.000
Thus, we will have a so-called development action menu,

05:47.000 --> 05:50.000
or individual development plans.

05:50.000 --> 05:57.000
When we have certain methods for the development of a certain competence.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
Remember, we had an assessment matrix there.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
How can we assess competencies?

06:01.000 --> 06:02.000
The same thing here.

06:02.000 --> 06:06.000
The matrix of development actions.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.000
How can we develop this competence?

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
What methods do we have?

06:11.000 --> 06:13.000
The methods can be completely different.

06:13.000 --> 06:17.000
It can be self-learning, it can be mentorship,

06:17.000 --> 06:21.000
as one of the most effective methods.

06:21.000 --> 06:24.000
It can be participation in development projects,

06:24.000 --> 06:27.000
training and seminar.

06:27.000 --> 06:33.000
It can be participation or even holding some master classes,

06:33.000 --> 06:36.000
most likely within the company.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
It's not that we send an employee to teach someone,

06:38.000 --> 06:44.000
but we say that if he has some professional knowledge,

06:44.000 --> 06:49.000
and on the other hand, he needs to develop the competence related to communication,

06:49.000 --> 06:54.000
work, let's say, a speech in front of an audience, and so on,

06:54.000 --> 06:58.000
then why not share his knowledge in this format?

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
It can be a development center.

07:00.000 --> 07:04.000
We talked about assessment centers.

07:04.000 --> 07:08.000
There is also a concept of a development center.

07:08.000 --> 07:13.000
The algorithm of the assessment is similar,

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
but the goal is different.

07:16.000 --> 07:23.000
The goal is not to assess, but to train.

07:23.000 --> 07:27.000
When an employee performs an exercise,

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
he immediately receives feedback.

07:29.000 --> 07:32.000
Then, within the framework of the development center,

07:32.000 --> 07:36.000
he receives another exercise and an opportunity to demonstrate and improve his skills.

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
The goal is not just to collect some information,

07:39.000 --> 07:44.000
but to let the employee try to change his behavior

07:44.000 --> 07:49.000
taking into account the feedback he received from the observers.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
It is important to remember that employees with high grades,

07:52.000 --> 07:55.000
that is, with a high level of competence development,

07:55.000 --> 07:56.000
regardless of their position,

07:56.000 --> 08:02.000
they can and should perform as functional coaches and mentors.

08:02.000 --> 08:05.000
Moreover, it is a great advantage for the company

08:05.000 --> 08:11.000
when the most valuable knowledge can be passed from one employee to another.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.000
It is also a plus for the employee, a kind of advantage,

08:13.000 --> 08:17.000
because it is connected with his inner motivation,

08:17.000 --> 08:21.000
including the fact that he becomes an internal or functional coach.

08:21.000 --> 08:25.000
Not to mention that if the company has a mentor stimulation system,

08:25.000 --> 08:31.000
it will always be an additional benefit.

08:31.000 --> 08:34.000
Speaking of competence development,

08:34.000 --> 08:39.000
we cannot help but talk about the competencies that are difficult to develop.

08:39.000 --> 08:42.000
Some people call them undeveloped competencies,

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
but this name probably has a certain predisposition,

08:45.000 --> 08:47.000
because if we call it competence,

08:47.000 --> 08:51.000
we must accept that what has grown has grown.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
What level of competence development does the employee have?

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
We should always work with this.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
Of course, there is a part of irony in this,

08:58.000 --> 09:02.000
because undeveloped competencies are those competencies,

09:02.000 --> 09:06.000
within which it is quite difficult to change a person's behavior.

09:06.000 --> 09:11.000
Nevertheless, we must understand whether such competencies exist in our model.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
Loyalty.

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
How much can it be? How will we evaluate it?

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
How will we develop it?

09:18.000 --> 09:22.000
How can we tell a person to be loyal if we want him to behave this way?

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
It's not that simple.

09:24.000 --> 09:26.000
Such competencies can be different.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
For example, the competence of creativity.

09:28.000 --> 09:31.000
Competencies are not often found.

09:31.000 --> 09:34.000
It can be found in small creative organizations,

09:34.000 --> 09:38.000
or it can be a professional competence of a group of employees.

09:38.000 --> 09:42.000
Nevertheless, at the stage of the formulation of competencies,

09:42.000 --> 09:45.000
answering the question of how we can analyze

09:45.000 --> 09:48.000
and whether we can develop this competence in the future,

09:48.000 --> 09:51.000
we should think about it.

09:51.000 --> 09:56.000
And, consequently, understand that it is one of such competencies.

09:56.000 --> 09:59.000
What tools do we have?

09:59.000 --> 10:05.000
The first is to analyze and select people at the entrance to the company for these competencies.

10:05.000 --> 10:10.000
That is, not to miss people who do not have the level that we need,

10:10.000 --> 10:12.000
if this competence is a priority.

10:12.000 --> 10:15.000
Also, develop a system of stimulation.

10:15.000 --> 10:19.000
If we use not only development tools,

10:19.000 --> 10:21.000
but also tools from another field,

10:21.000 --> 10:24.000
that is, the behavior that we consider necessary.

10:24.000 --> 10:29.000
And also, try to determine the methods that may be.

10:29.000 --> 10:31.000
Among them there may be coaching,

10:31.000 --> 10:34.000
among which there must be feedback.

10:34.000 --> 10:38.000
If a person is interested in developing this competence,

10:38.000 --> 10:40.000
he has an inner desire,

10:40.000 --> 10:42.000
then this method will be very effective,

10:42.000 --> 10:45.000
because he will receive feedback from a colleague,

10:45.000 --> 10:48.000
from a manager, or from some internal expert.

10:48.000 --> 10:55.000
And he will change and consciously change his activity in the direction that is necessary.

10:55.000 --> 10:58.000
A few words about the personnel reserve,

10:58.000 --> 11:00.000
which we have already talked about today.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
First of all, it is necessary to determine for ourselves

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
what we understand as a personnel reserve.

11:05.000 --> 11:11.000
Historically, we understand the personnel reserve as a reserve for a position,

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
for any of the positions.

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
It can be either a management reserve,

11:16.000 --> 11:19.000
that is, when specialists are formed,

11:19.000 --> 11:23.000
reservists are formed for the position of a manager,

11:23.000 --> 11:25.000
or from the manager of the lower link,

11:25.000 --> 11:32.000
a reserve is formed for the position of a higher level manager.

11:32.000 --> 11:37.000
Nevertheless, there is a concept that has become part of our language today,

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
which we read a lot in literature.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
It is the management of talents.

11:42.000 --> 11:45.000
When we form the so-called talent pool,

11:45.000 --> 11:47.000
what is it about?

11:47.000 --> 11:50.000
Is there any difference?

11:50.000 --> 11:53.000
Most often, those companies that adhere to this principle

11:53.000 --> 11:57.000
and say that we are not just forming a reserve for a certain position.

11:57.000 --> 12:02.000
No, we select talented specialists from different fields.

12:02.000 --> 12:06.000
We evaluate them by defining a talent for ourselves in a certain way,

12:06.000 --> 12:09.000
and most often as a potential for development.

12:09.000 --> 12:13.000
We already understand that this is a certain set of competencies.

12:13.000 --> 12:16.000
We define these people for ourselves

12:16.000 --> 12:21.000
in order to pay more attention to them during our work with the staff

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
and understand that this is our future

12:23.000 --> 12:27.000
and that it is more efficient for us to invest in this particular category of employees.

12:27.000 --> 12:32.000
In this case, the talent pool is not for a specific position.

12:32.000 --> 12:36.000
There is no profile of the competence of the chief engineer,

12:36.000 --> 12:39.000
the reserve for which we are forming.

12:39.000 --> 12:42.000
There is a certain scope for the future,

12:42.000 --> 12:47.000
or a certain profile of success, as some companies call it.

12:47.000 --> 12:51.000
Thus, it is necessary to define the direction in which we work.

12:51.000 --> 12:54.000
Either we have a reserve for a position,

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
or for a managerial position,

12:56.000 --> 12:59.000
or for a position of a specialist, a rare specialist,

12:59.000 --> 13:01.000
who is almost not on the market.

13:01.000 --> 13:05.000
Let's say a technologist in our tricky production.

13:05.000 --> 13:08.000
And we grow all technologists on our own.

13:08.000 --> 13:11.000
Or, once again, a talent pool.

13:11.000 --> 13:15.000
In any case, we understand that we select candidates

13:15.000 --> 13:19.000
for the pool and the reserve based on the results of evaluation events.

13:19.000 --> 13:22.000
We create individual development plans.

13:22.000 --> 13:26.000
Only if we understand what to include in the development plan,

13:26.000 --> 13:29.000
because there is a profile of the position,

13:29.000 --> 13:32.000
in the reserve for which they are included,

13:32.000 --> 13:36.000
and we understand, comparing with their current profile,

13:36.000 --> 13:39.000
what competencies need to be developed.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.000
As for the talent pool,

13:41.000 --> 13:45.000
we are talking about a certain profile of success.

13:45.000 --> 13:48.000
When we set a certain level,

13:48.000 --> 13:52.000
maybe we draw profiles of a young manager,

13:52.000 --> 13:56.000
or we define for ourselves in some other way.

13:56.000 --> 13:59.000
And we start from this profile,

13:59.000 --> 14:02.000
which we have defined for ourselves.

14:05.000 --> 14:09.000
For reservists, individual plans are made.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
And it is very important that people,

14:12.000 --> 14:16.000
who are listed in the reserve or in the talent pool,

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
are not just listed once,

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
but then in a year, two or three,

14:20.000 --> 14:22.000
to see what happened to them.

14:22.000 --> 14:24.000
These are people,

14:24.000 --> 14:26.000
who we invest more money in,

14:26.000 --> 14:28.000
from the calculation of one employee,

14:28.000 --> 14:30.000
than in other employees.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.000
Therefore, we need to constantly monitor

14:32.000 --> 14:34.000
the effectiveness of our investments.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.000
What does it mean?

14:36.000 --> 14:38.000
This is the level of reserve preparation.

14:38.000 --> 14:40.000
Six months have passed.

14:40.000 --> 14:43.000
We gave recommendations to employees.

14:43.000 --> 14:46.000
Did any change happen or not?

14:46.000 --> 14:50.000
This is something that must be monitored.

14:50.000 --> 14:52.000
There are two aspects.

14:52.000 --> 14:58.000
The first one is very slow and fast reserve preparation.

14:58.000 --> 15:02.000
If the reserve is medium-term,

15:02.000 --> 15:04.000
for example, for three years,

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
and we prepared it for a year,

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
but in a year we do not need

15:08.000 --> 15:10.000
any specialist in this area,

15:10.000 --> 15:12.000
what can happen?

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
Everything can turn out great.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
The employee will say thank you,

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
will spread his wings

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
and will continue his career in another organization.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.000
Therefore, you must feel this balance,

15:22.000 --> 15:24.000
initially programming the reserve period,

15:24.000 --> 15:26.000
for which we are preparing.

15:26.000 --> 15:28.000
The benefits that the organization gets

15:28.000 --> 15:30.000
when forming and developing the personnel reserve

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
cannot be overestimated.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
First of all,

15:34.000 --> 15:36.000
we must understand

15:36.000 --> 15:38.000
that this is a systematic and targeted development

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
of a certain group of employees.

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
That is, money is invested in the best.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
As we assume,

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
we do everything to maximize

15:46.000 --> 15:48.000
the return on these investments.

15:48.000 --> 15:50.000
The reservists themselves understand

15:50.000 --> 15:52.000
what the company expects from them

15:52.000 --> 15:54.000
if they have individual plans

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
or plans for future careers.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
Thus, the best of them

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
purposefully strive to meet these expectations.

16:00.000 --> 16:02.000
The second aspect is

16:02.000 --> 16:04.000
that the company is not a company

16:04.000 --> 16:06.000
that is based on expectations.

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
Further, the corporate culture of the company

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
is gradually changing.

16:10.000 --> 16:12.000
It becomes oriented to personal development,

16:12.000 --> 16:14.000
to initiative, to creativity.

16:14.000 --> 16:16.000
That is, it appears in the hands of

16:16.000 --> 16:18.000
linear managers and staff.

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
A real tool for working with employees

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
appears,

16:22.000 --> 16:24.000
increasing their loyalty

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
and involvement in business.

16:26.000 --> 16:28.000
It can also be said

16:28.000 --> 16:30.000
that there is a transition

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
of personnel service

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
to a different quality level of development.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
Thus, both the organization

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
and the personnel service

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
as a guide and an agent

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
of such changes win.

